      • handleUserCommand

        public java.lang.String handleUserCommand(java.lang.String message)
        ***NOTE BEFORE ADDING A COMMAND*** If you add a command, then please make sure it is in alphabetical order (exceptions include very similar commands (e.g. /ban and /unban)). Also, don't forget to document it with the /help function. Available Commands ban "[reason]" Ban's a player () for a specified time () (they can't log in or play) from the server. //TODO: Log the 'reason' or display it to user censor [on|off] Naughty words are "*"'d out (e.g. shit => ****) 0 Arguments: toggles censorship on or off. 1 Argument: turns censorship on or off. help [command] Displays the list of available commands or info on a particular command. 0 Arguments: displays list of ALL commands join Change to another channel (if it doesn't exist, create it) 1 Argument: move to or create the channel kick [reason] MOD ONLY: Remove a player from the server for a specified time with or without a reason. 2 Arguments: Removes player from server and bans for duration 3 Arguments: Same as 2 except logs a reason? logout Opens logout dialog mod [level] Displays or sets (if USER has the privilege) another user's privilege level. 1 Argument: display a player's privilege level 2 Arguments: set a player's privilege level (promote / demote) mute [[channel|server]] [duration]] Stop a player's text from showing up on your client or, prevent a player from writing anything in the chat (if USER has the privilege). 1 Argument: mute a player locally 2 Arguments: mute a player in a channel or server permanently 3 Arguments: mute a player in a channel or server for a specified time players Displays a list of players who are online tploc tpxy MOD ONLY: tp MOD ONLY: tpme MOD ONLY: unmute [[server]|[channel]] quit Rage quit the game. qq See quit.
        Parameters:
        message - The message to handled from the user.
        Returns:
        response Strign response (outcome of the command).
